The paper deals with the design of space-time codes for cooperative relay channels and MIMO-OFDM channels. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of space-time codes in parallel multi-block channels, which could be classified under computer communications (cs.CC) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the concept of approximate universality, which could be classified under social and information networks (cs.SI).
